-- Barclays Hires Marco Oviedo as Chief Economist for Mexico
-- B y   V e r o n i c a   N a v a r r o   E s p i n o s a
-- 2012-06-21T20:19:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-21/barclays-hires-marco-oviedo-as-chief-economist-for-mexico.html
Barclays Plc (BARC)  said it hired Marco Oviedo as its chief economist for Mexico.  Oviedo previously worked as chief economic adviser for the
staff of President Felipe Calderon, according to an internal
memo obtained by Bloomberg. Seth Martin, a bank spokesman,
confirmed the contents of the memo.  Oviedo will be based in Mexico City and report to Marcelo
Salomon, Martin said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Veronica Navarro Espinosa in New York at 
 vespinosa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
